commentTextItems.html: short and just enough width for Franklin to cut backward of square for four

commentPostTextItems.html: New Zealand take the match by three wickets and the series 3-0. It was a valliant display by Bangladesh who really made the hosts work hard for victory today.
Imrul's maiden ODI century was the highlight of the match and although Guptill made a sparkling 91, it was a shame to see him give it away when three figures were beckoning.

Shakib bowled nicely, taking four for 33, and, it seems, he is learning how to bowl on New Zealand's pitches, especially when you consider how different the condtions are compared to his tracks at home.

For New Zealand, Southee (3 for 37) and Vettori (3 for 42) were the pick of the bowlers. Vettori will be a little disappointed with how they chased the mediocre total, but having said that, you can't ask for too much more than a 3-0 series victory. Shakib and Bangladesh will take a lot of heart out of their performance tonight and , if they could've added an extra 20-30 runs at the death, the match would've been far tighter and they weren't too far away.
The Man of the Match is Martin Guptill for his run-a-ball 91 which was the backbone of ew Zealand's chase.
We now look forward to the one-off Test match which starts in Hamilton on Monday. You can join us for live coverage of the Test which starts at 11am local time or 2200 (Sunday) GMT.
On behalf of the crew here at Cricinfo this is Marc Ellison saying thanks for joining us for the ODI series, we look forward to your company again on Monday. All the very best and goodnight.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Ashraful c †McCullum b Oram 31 (55b 4x4 0x6 65m) SR: 56.36

dismissalComment.html: Ashraful is in two minds here and tries to push to third man, it takes the edge and McCullum dives full stretch to right right and plucks the ball out of the air with one hand. Super catch!

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan c Taylor b Southee 36 (48b 3x4 0x6 68m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: good length from Southee is onto Shakib quicker than he expected and as he looks to heave it over mid wicket, gets it high on the bat and skies it to Taylor running in from mid wicket

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim lbw b Vettori 4 (14b 0x4 0x6 20m) SR: 28.57

dismissalComment.html: quick and full and Mushfiq tries to sweep but misses and is hit dead in front. Not a difficult decision for Gary Baxter to give that out!

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah b Vettori 6 (6b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: gives himself a little room and just plays inside the line and is bowled. Pretty soft looking dismissal.

dismissalText.commentary: Martin Guptill c Tamim Iqbal b Shakib Al Hasan 91 (91b 9x4 3x6 109m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: Guptill gives himself room again and tries to hit it high over long off but gets it too flat and straight to long off where Tamim accepts the catch

dismissalText.commentary: Ross Taylor st †Mushfiqur Rahim b Shakib Al Hasan 3 (10b 0x4 0x6 15m) SR: 30

dismissalComment.html: Taylor uses his feet again but Shakib beats him with flight and turn as he tries to play through the leg side and Mushfiq has ample time to take the bails off. Vital wicket for Bangladesh!

stories.title: Vettori confident about smooth transition into whites
stories.subTitle: New Zealand v Bangladesh, 3rd ODI, Christchurch
stories.seoTitle: Daniel Vettori confident about smooth transition into whites
stories.summary: Daniel Vettori admitted to misreading the pitch at the AMI Stadium, which contributed to a close finish to the third ODI, but was pleased with his bowlers' performance

stories.summary: Bangladesh and Shakib Al Hasan turned in their best performance of the tour, but is was still not enough to prevent New Zealand from sweeping the series
